From: SideloadTool Android Fix <fix@sideload.tool>
Date: Sat, 19 Jul 2026 04:45:00 +0700
Subject: [PATCH] libusbmuxd: fix connect_usbmuxd_socket() for Android Unix paths

On Android, USBMUXD_SOCKET_ADDRESS is set to a Unix socket path like
/data/user/0/.../usbmuxd.sock without the "UNIX:" prefix.

The current code only handles:
  1. "UNIX:/path/to/socket"  → socket_connect_unix(path)
  2. "host:port"             → TCP socket_connect()

But Android apps set the path directly without prefix, and the path
contains no ':' so it falls through to the default /var/run/usbmuxd,
which doesn't exist on Android → connection fails → IDEVICE_E_NO_DEVICE.

Fix: Add a check for absolute Unix paths (starting with '/') when
USBMUXD_SOCKET_ADDRESS is set but has no prefix and no ':'.

--- a/src/libusbmuxd.c
+++ b/src/libusbmuxd.c
@@ -164,6 +164,20 @@ static int connect_usbmuxd_socket()
 	int res = -1;
 	char *usbmuxd_socket_addr = getenv("USBMUXD_SOCKET_ADDRESS");
 	if (usbmuxd_socket_addr) {
+		/* FIX: Android non-root — Unix path without UNIX: prefix */
+		if (usbmuxd_socket_addr[0] == '/') {
+#if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
+			/* not supported, ignore */
+#else
+			res = socket_connect_unix(usbmuxd_socket_addr);
+			if (res < 0) {
+				res = -errno;
+			}
+			return res;
+#endif
+		}
+		/* Existing UNIX: prefix handling */
 		if (strncmp(usbmuxd_socket_addr, "UNIX:", 5) == 0) {
 #if defined(_WIN32) || defined(__CYGWIN__)
 			/* not supported, ignore */
